      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study conducted on the screw-rod assembly. Stiffness QoI changes 1.3% between medium (420k elements) and fine (1.1M elements) meshes. GCI computed at 2.8% for stiffness and 3.4% for yield force. Fine mesh adopted for all production runs. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver residual tolerances and iterative convergence criteria documented and shown to be sufficient for the nonlinear contact problem.",
      "rationale": "The assessment team concluded that numerical solver error does not materially apply to this COU because the commercial solver (Ansys Mechanical) employs automatic load-stepping and residual monitoring by default, and prior internal studies have not identified solver-induced discrepancies in quasi-static contact problems of this class. Accordingly, no formal solver error assessment — including documentation of residual tolerances, convergence histories, or sensitivity to solver settings — was performed. This reasoning conflates engineering judgment with a formal assessment finding; the correct encoding would be 'not-applicable' only if a documented scope exclusion argument were provided. At modelRiskLevel 3, the absence of a formal assessment leaves a material gap in the credibility evidence."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
