      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test constructs from production lots; traceability of each specimen to material certificates documented.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories (n=6 Lab A, n=5 Lab B). All specimens drawn from production lots with full material traceability. Dimensional inspection confirms all specimens within drawing tolerances. Sample size sufficient for statistical comparison per ASME V&V 40 Table 5-1 Gradation 3 criteria. Gradation 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions replicate COU loading environment; multiple load levels or boundary condition variants explored.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed strictly per ASTM F1717 protocol at a single load configuration (compression-bending, 10° offset). While the protocol is the regulatory standard for this device class, only one test condition was evaluated; no parametric variation in offset angle, load rate, or environmental conditioning (e.g., saline immersion) was performed. This limits the factor to Gradation 2. The description in the COU package acknowledges this shortfall. Required level 3 not achieved; gap noted and accepted at Medium assurance level."
    },
