      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) directly correspond to regulatory submission requirements and clinical failure modes.",
      "rationale": "The three QoIs are explicitly required by FDA guidance for pedicle screw submissions under ASTM F1717. Stiffness governs load transfer to the fusion segment; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement bracket the clinically relevant failure envelope. No auxiliary or surrogate QoIs substituted. Gradation 3 achieved."
